description:
In lichen_l2_input() at lichen_l2.c:435-439, a 16-byte link key is copied to a stack buffer:

    uint8_t rx_link_key[LICHEN_LINK_KEY_LEN];
    if (link_ctx.has_link_key) {
        memcpy(rx_link_key, link_ctx.link_key, LICHEN_LINK_KEY_LEN);
        rx_link_key_ptr = rx_link_key;
    }

After lichen_link_rx() completes, rx_link_key is never zeroized. The key remains on the stack until overwritten.

Impact: The link key is a symmetric key used for AES-CCM-64 MIC generation. An attacker with stack read capability (debugger, stack overflow read, memory corruption) could recover the link key and forge authenticated frames.

Fix: Add explicit_bzero(rx_link_key, sizeof(rx_link_key)) before each return path after line 439, or use a cleanup label/goto pattern.

Location: firmware/bridge-zephyr/subsys/lichen/lichen_l2.c:435-439, with fix needed before returns at lines 455-457, 479-480, 487-490
